Dia. 04 Black Lives
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Against Black \'a1\'e3, it is not good if White plays hane at 1.
\par Black 2 is a \cf1\b good move\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par Shall we check what is the meaning of this move?
\par Against White 3, Black 4 works and after White 5, Black plays dansu at 6 and it becomes \cf2\b continuous dansu\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par Therefore White 2 is the only move in \b Dia. 03\b0 .
\par
\par }
